last_episode_to_air.name: Episode 2
last_episode_to_air.overview: Adrian learns fascinating history at mainland Ireland's most northerly tip, from Marconi's wireless messages to signs that helped WWII pilots. After a scenic railway journey, he visits the legendary Giant's Causeway and samples short horn beef. Along Strangford Lough, he tours Mount Stewart's magnificent gardens before ending in the majestic Mourne Mountains, CS Lewis's inspiration for Narnia.

name: Adrian Dunbar's Coastal Ireland
overview: Actor Adrian Dunbar reconnects with his roots as he travels around the wild and rugged Irish coast.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: Adrian's journey starts in the south at Mizen Head, where waves reach astounding heights. After visiting a friend in Cork, he sails to the Skellig Islands, home to monastic ruins seen in Star Wars. On the Aran Islands, he tours a clifftop prehistoric fort before hitting Donegal's beaches to chat with a founding father of Irish surfing. In County Sligo, he pays tribute to great Irish poet WB Yates.
